com.mapzen.tangram

Class Marker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mapzen.tangram.Marker

  • public class Marker
extends java.lang.Object
    Class used to display points, polylines, and bitmaps dynamically on a map. Do not create one of these objects directly, instead use MapController.addMarker().

      • setStylingFromPath

        public boolean setStylingFromPath(java.lang.String path)
        Used to style the marker Sets draw rules from a draw group of a scene layer in the scene file, used to load the scene. This draw group must be defined in the loaded scene file.
        • layers.layer_a.layer_b.draw.some_draw_rule
        • layers.layer_c.draw.another_draw_rule
        Parameters:
        path - Absolute path to a draw rule in the current scene, delimited with "."
        Returns:
        whether the styling was successfully set on the marker.

      • setStylingFromString

        public boolean setStylingFromString(java.lang.String styleString)
        Used to style the marker Sets the styling to be used to display either a point, polyline, or bitmap for this marker. If the marker is going to be used to display a bitmap, a 'points' style must be set.
        • { style: 'points', color: 'white', size: [50px, 50px], order: 2000, collide: false }
        • { style: 'lines', color: '#06a6d4', width: 5px, order: 2000 }
        • { style: 'polygons', color: '#06a6d4', width: 5px, order: 2000 }
        Parameters:
        styleStr - the style string
        Returns:
        whether the style was successfully set

      • setDrawable

        public boolean setDrawable(int drawableId)
        Sets the drawable resource id to be used to load a bitmap. When displaying a drawable, a 'points' style must also be set on the marker (see Marker#setStyling(String).
        Parameters:
        drawableId - the drawable resource id
        Returns:
        whether the drawable's bitmap was successfully set
